# Functions
classes.py
- all data processing and file parsing

Variable_Node : class object for each child node
attributes include parents, domains, conditional probability table

Model : class object that holds the vars and creates joint CPT's

parse_input_file : read input file data and build basic node attributes

create_big_cpt : calculates joint probability distribution for each node


bayes_net.py
Bayes_Net : class object for running the algorithms

enumeration_ask : function to calculate odds of query var given optional evidence

enumerate_all : function to calculate all possibilities for joint CPT

normalize : takes a dictionary and returns a distribution

print_output : prints normalized values such as   ([books.txt] input: "Recommendation | Quality = 1")

P(1) = 0.602, P(2) = 0.089, P(3) = 0.101, P(4) = 0.125, P(5) = 0.083


Joint CPT examples

Parents: Burglary, Earthquake
Child: Alarm

B E A : Probability : Alarm
T.T.T : v = 0.95
T.T.F : v = 0.05
T.F.T : v = 0.94
T.F.F : v = 0.06
F.T.T : v = 0.29
F.T.F : v = 0.71
F.F.T : v = 0.001
F.F.F : v = 0.999

Parents: Sprinkler, Rain
Child: Wetgrass

S R W : Probability : Wetgrass
F.F.T : v = 1.0
F.F.F : v = 0.0
T.F.T : v = 0.1
T.F.F : v = 0.9
F.T.T : v = 0.1
F.T.F : v = 0.9
T.T.T : v = 0.01
T.T.F : v = 0.99

